external_knowledge:
- 'vibrant sectors' refers to sectors with weights greater than the average sector weight; 
- 'beacons of light' metaphorically refers to plans that stand out due to their significant budget and time frame (2000-2005);
- 'dawn of the new millennium' refers to the start year 2000;
- 'culminating before the mid-point of the same decade' means ending by the year 2005;
- 'threshold of fifteen million dollars' refers to the budget exceeding 15,000,000.

sql:
SELECT plan_name
FROM plans
WHERE plan_id = 1;

SELECT sectors.sector_name, sector_indicators.indicator_value
FROM sectors
JOIN sector_indicators ON sectors.sector_id = sector_indicators.sector_id;

SELECT indicator_name, indicator_value
FROM sector_indicators
WHERE indicator_name LIKE 'Indicator%';

SELECT plan_sector_target_id, target_id
FROM plan_sector_targets
WHERE target_end_value > 4.0;

SELECT user_name, role
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT DISTINCT created_by FROM plans);

external_knowledge:
- "seeds" refers to achievements;
- "bloomed into flowers" symbolizes the completion of achievements;
- "expected blossoms" means the target end values set for the sectors within plans;
- "gardens" refers to the sectors;
- "narratives of these triumphs" corresponds to the detailed descriptions of the achievements.

- "lofty goals" refers to target values greater than 50,000;
- "significant achievement marks" refers to achievement values greater than 40,000;
- "last two decades" refers to plans starting from 2000 to 2020.

- 'prolific users' refers to users who have a significant number of reports;
- 'couple of reports' implies two or fewer reports;
- 'combined budget surpassing a thousand' means the total budget is greater than 1000.

sql:
SELECT u.user_name, p.plan_name
FROM plans p
INNER JOIN users u ON p.created_by = u.user_id;

SELECT sector_name, sector_weight
FROM sectors
WHERE sector_weight > (SELECT AVG(sector_weight) FROM sectors);

SELECT plan_name, main_objective, status
FROM plans
WHERE plan_name = '1st' AND start_year BETWEEN 1950 AND 1959;
